  "datePublished": "2026-03-08",
  "description": "GGUF (GPT-Generated Unified Format) is a binary file format for storing quantized neural network weights alongside all metadata needed to load and run them. It was created by the llama.cpp project, replacing the older GGML format.\nA single GGUF file is self-contained: it holds the model weights, tokenizer data, architecture parameters, and configuration. This makes it portable — one file is everything needed to run the model. GGUF supports quantization at 2-bit through 8-bit precision and is designed for memory-mapped loading, so the operating system can stream parts of the model from disk rather than loading everything into RAM at once.\n",
  "name": "GGUF",
